OL,4,Cthree killed by timber-load lorry fall
OL,6,FThe court also heard how there had
OL,7,Fbeen previous incidents of loads
OL,8,Fcoming off during travel, including
OL,9,Fthree steel bars that fell off and
OL,10,Fstruck another car but did not injure
OL,11,Fanyone in April 2019.
OL,13,FIt was also raised the driver in May
OL,14,F2020 had been involved in previous
OL,15,Fincidents in his five-year employment,
OL,16,Fwhich had been reported but on one
OL,17,Foccasion not recorded, and another
OL,18,Finstance a need for training was
OL,19,Fflagged but there was "no clear
OL,20,Fevidence" the company could know the
OL,21,Ftraining had been learnt by the driver.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/12
